body:
Yep, which is what happens now in this PR.
The thing is: if any non Python-using header is included first, then those symbols get defined in some c++ header and we get the warning as soon as we hit the first Python.h include.
So we must ensure that Python.h is the first thing to be included in a python-enabled build.
